## How Encoding Works

1. User uploads a cover image.
2. User enters a secret message.
3. User selects a steganographic profile.
4. Optional password encryption is applied for K8.
5. Message is converted into binary format.
6. Binary bits are embedded into image pixels.
7. A stego-image is generated and returned.

---

## How Decoding Works

1. User uploads a stego-image.
2. User selects the correct profile.
3. User enters password if encryption was used.
4. Binary data is extracted from image pixels.
5. Hidden message is reconstructed.
6. Original text is displayed.

